column1: Garbagnate Milanese (Lombard: Garbagnaa [ɡarbaˈɲɑː]) is a comune (municipality) in the Metropolitan City of Milan in the Italian region Lombardy
column2: located about 15 kilometres (9 mi) northwest of Milan.

column1: Garbagnate Milanese borders the following municipalities: Caronno Pertusella
Garbagnate received the honorary title of city with a presidential decree on February 25
